examples.en: She exhibited her paintings to the public.
The patient exhibited signs of the disease.
He exhibited a bright example of the most heroic valour.
He exhibited a brazen disregard for other people's feelings.
He first exhibited an interest in music when he was very young.
A facsimile of the world's first computer was exhibited in the museum.
The couple exhibited poor etiquette when they left the party without saying good-bye to the host and hostess.
